    "notes": [
      "invitatory: Ps 95 every morning, with Ps 100, Ps 67, or Ps 24 as permitted alternatives.",
      "officeOfReadings seasonal variants: Sat wk1, Sat wk2, Fri wk4, Sat wk4 differ between Advent/Christmas/Lent/Easter ('advent-christmas-lent-easter') and Ordinary Time ('ordinary-time'), per GILH 130 (Pss 78, 105, 106 reserved for the strong seasons).",
      "morningPrayer (Lauds) pattern: psalm, OT canticle, psalm.",
      "eveningPrayer (Vespers) pattern: psalm, psalm, NT canticle. Saturday evening is EP-I of the following Sunday; Sunday evening is EP-II.",
      "Sunday EP-II NT canticle: Rev 19:1-7, replaced by 1 Pet 2:21-24 in Lent (all four weeks).",
      "daytimePrayer: one hour with the psalms listed; if praying all three little hours (Terce/Sext/None), the other two use the complementary psalmody series.",
      "nightPrayer (Compline) has a one-week cycle by day, not a four-week cycle. Saturday Compline follows EP-I of Sunday.",
      "CAUTION: wk4 Thursday officeOfReadings duplicates wk2 Thursday (Ps 44) in the source table; plausible but worth double-checking against a printed breviary before flipping verified:true on that one day."
    ]
  },
